helpdesk-note.body: Any updates on this ticket?
helpdesk-note.body-html: Any updates on this ticket?

helpdesk-note.body:
From Jenzabar:
Nicole,
Can you try this?
ERROR 35: Error calling external object function open at line 9 in function
of_open_file_of object n_ole_wp_word_97.
Problems with Mail Merge and getting the above error.
1. IF the Merge Data File is on the network (usually other than C: or D:)m make sure the Merge Data File starts with \\ and includes the entire path name. A mapped drive will not work on this line. Example: \\upton\documents\development\ instead of M:\development. Mapped drives (M:\development) will work on the PBL name and the Merge Document Name.
2. If the Merge Data File lines are set up correctly and you are still receiving this error, you will have to change the name of the documents. Example: If FRTY is giving this error, right click in the Merge Documents field and select Add row. Set up a new letter code of FRTYA. Give FTRYA the same PBL, same Merge Data File, aame Merge Document Info. Save your changes. Now replace FTRY with FRTYA in the letter to send field (for the letter code receiving the error). IHCQJgW�vR1��

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Zachary Sauve,
Firstly, all MSOE staff and faculty have access to the H drive. However, MSOE laptops do not come with the network drives already mapped, so you probably have to map a network drive to be able to see it. Here is a guide on how to map a network drive. Select drive H, and in the Folded field, type "\\homestore\homedrives$\username" (type your username, don't include the quotes). Follow the direction in the provided link. Let us know if this does not solve your problem.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Zachary Sauve,

Firstly, all MSOE staff and faculty have access to the H drive. However, MSOE laptops do not come with the network drives already mapped, so you probably have to map a network drive to be able to see it. Here is a guide on how to map a network drive. 
Select drive H, and in the Folded field, type "\\homestore\homedrives$\username" (type your username, don't include the quotes).
Follow the direction in the provided link. Let us know if this does not solve your problem.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: Advisor Accounts
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good morning—
We are having an issue with our three front computers that we use to serve the students who come to our office.
When our office is busy, like today for the drop deadline or starting next week for registration, we all jump in to help at the counter as needed. However, each person can now only be logged into the Jenzabar remote desktop on one computer. So, to help students at the front counter, we either need to bring students back to our desks…which are usually covered with confidential information that shouldn’t be viewed by other students, or we need to get out of whatever we are in the middle of working on at our desks so that we can log in at the front computers which just isn’t a realistic possibility for most of us if we want to get any work done. Neither solution is a good option.
Back on January 8th, the solution seemed to be that our student workers would be given their own remote desktop. As I explained at that time, since only one of them is working at a time, that doesn’t really help the situation. Our option at this point is to have the workstudy student who works the first shift of the day log in and then we try to keep that computer from timing out for the rest of the day.
If there is no solution, we will need to completely change the way we do customer service during registration. So, I can’t wait much longer for an update on this.
Thanks.
Mary
Mary Nielsen Registrar Milwaukee School of Engineering

helpdesk-ticket.subject: H drive files not synchronizing across machines to classroom machines
helpdesk-ticket.description: In my office this morning I saved a file to my H drive with the intent of accessing it in class from one of the built in pc’s. When I arrived in class, I was able to log on to the machine, but the file was not present on the h drive of the machine. Upon arriving back in my office, I was able to again see that the file had been stored to the h drive and was safely in the location I had placed it.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: In my office this morning I saved a file to my H drive with the intent of accessing it in class from one of the built in pc’s.  When I arrived in class, I was able to log on to the machine, but the file was not present on the h drive of the machine.  Upon arriving back in my office, I was able to again see that the file had been stored to the h drive and was safely in the location I had placed it.

helpdesk-note.body:
Dr. Schilling,
I am unable to reproduce this issue. I saved a word document file to my H drive and walked downstairs to CC210 and logged into the classroom podium as myself. The recently saved file was there and I could access it successfully. I spoke with Michael Timm to try and come up with any scenarios where the file might not have been saved. Is it a large file? a VM or something like that? There is no synching or anything because it is just another file system and what ever you saved should have been there right away. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi zietlows,
I suggest you try to uninstall and reinstall Global Protect. In my experience, it tends to malfunction when not fully updated.
You can uninstall it by clicking on "Computer" in the file explorer, then choosing the option at the top of the window that says "Uninstall or Change Programs". Select your Global Protect Program, and choose "Uninstall".
To reinstall Global Protect, you need to log into the vpn portal at https://sslvpn.msoe.edu. Once you are in, select the Windows 64 bit download, and run the setup program when it finishes downloading. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5157
The user is trying to use AutoCAD at home through the VPN. In doing so he recieves a license error. This only happens when he is on the GlobalProtect VPN. The information for the VPN has been checked to be correct.

Hi zietlows,

I suggest you try to uninstall and reinstall Global Protect. In my experience, it tends to malfunction when not fully updated. 

You can uninstall it by clicking on "Computer" in the file explorer, then choosing the option at the top of the window that says "Uninstall or Change Programs". Select your Global Protect Program, and choose "Uninstall".

To reinstall Global Protect, you need to log into the vpn portal at https://sslvpn.msoe.edu. Once you are in, select the Windows 64 bit download, and run the setup program when it finishes downloading.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi weis,
I have tested every audio connection in the room and they are all operational. Please make sure if you are using either the HDMI or DisplayPort connection to set the playback device on your laptop to output to "Crestron" by following the steps below. Please let me know if you have anymore issues with this.
1.)After connecting HDMI/DisplayPort cable to laptop, press the windows key and type "manage audio devices" and select Manage Audio Devices
2.) Select "Crestron" device from Playback menu and click "Set Default" in the right hand corner
3.) Crestron device should now have a green check mark by it to show that it is now sending to the device
4.) Once the Crestron device is set to default the audio is now being output to the speakers in the room
Thanks, Tim Koruna

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi meiser, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5177 I am trying to upload videos to the MSOE show and share portal https://video.msoe.edu/vportal/VideoPlayer.jsp?ccsid=C-46bba3de-64c6-467c-ba76-15a53304ac8e:1# and it is saying they can't connect to the server.
It looks like chrome isn't supporting the encryption its using. Hard to tell if its temporary or permanent as chrome does like to switch things up on a daily basis.
It works fine in IE, so for today i would say use that. I will look into it more. And update this ticket later this week.
Tony

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Alumni Access For Community
helpdesk-ticket.description: User is unable to switch account from msoe account to alumni account due to his msoe account being disabled after graduation. Needs his account switched to alumni status
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: User is unable to switch account from msoe account to alumni account due to his msoe account being disabled after graduation. Needs his account switched to alumni status

helpdesk-note.body:
For a user to switch their account from an @msoe.edu email to @alumni.msoe.edu, the following steps should be taken:
1. Go to https://www.msoe.edu/switcher_app/ 2. Click on Switch from MSOE to Alumni Login 3. Enter your current Community information (@msoe.edu, for example). If you do not remember the password, please click on “Forgot Community Password”. Click Login. 4. Enter your new email (@alumni.msoe.edu, for example) 5. Click SUBMIT
helpdesk-note.body-html:
For a user to switch their account from an @msoe.edu email to @alumni.msoe.edu, the following steps should be taken:

1. Go to https://www.msoe.edu/switcher_app/
2. Click on Switch from MSOE to Alumni Login
3. Enter your current Community information (@msoe.edu, for example).  If you do not remember the password, please click on “Forgot Community Password”.  Click Login. 
4. Enter your new email (@alumni.msoe.edu, for example)
5. Click SUBMIT

helpdesk-note.body:
Dear Scott,
Thank you for your patience with your community account.
In order to change your MSOE Community account from your @msoe.edu email address to your @alumni.msoe.edu address, we ask that you do the following:
1. Go to https://www.msoe.edu/switcher_app/ 2. Click on Switch from MSOE to Alumni Login 3. Enter your current Community information (@msoe.edu, for example). If you do not remember the password, please click on “Forgot Community Password”. Click Login. This step must be taken even though your @msoe.edu email account was disabled. 4. Enter your new email (@alumni.msoe.edu, for example) 5. Click SUBMIT
Please let us know if this process was successful for you. We can continue to troubleshoot the situation, if needed. Sincerely, Dana Grennier Digital Marketing ----------------------------------
Hi Scott Sutton, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5181
User is unable to switch account from msoe account to alumni account due to his msoe account being disabled after graduation. Needs his account switched to alumni status
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Dear Scott,

Thank you for your patience with your community account.  

In order to change your MSOE Community account from your @msoe.edu email address to your @alumni.msoe.edu address, we ask that you do the following:

1. Go to https://www.msoe.edu/switcher_app/
2. Click on Switch from MSOE to Alumni Login
3. Enter your current Community information (@msoe.edu, for example).  If you do not remember the password, please click on “Forgot Community Password”.  Click Login. This step must be taken even though your @msoe.edu email account was disabled.
4. Enter your new email (@alumni.msoe.edu, for example)
5. Click SUBMIT

Please let us know if this process was successful for you.  We can continue to troubleshoot the situation, if needed.
Sincerely,
Dana Grennier
Digital Marketing

Done W: Failed to fetch http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/dists/trusty/InRelease W: Failed to fetch http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/dists/trusty-updates/InRelease
Rob

helpdesk-note.body: Dear IT, Thank you for your assistance in putting up a wall mounted TV. I do have a few questions/concerns. First, in order to be viewable by all families, a wall mount that can pull out the TV and can move from side to side, may be better than the one that is currently in placed. helpdesk-note.body-html:
Dear IT,

Thank you for your assistance in putting up a wall mounted TV. I do have a few questions/concerns. 

First, in order to be viewable by all families, a wall mount that can pull out the TV and can move from side to side, may be better than the one that is currently in placed. If this was misunderstood at the initial request, I apologize for the miscommunication.

Second, the powerpoint presentation is currently on a timer. For presenting purposes, counselors would need the ability to manually control the powerpoint. Is this possible to do for the wall mounted TV that has been provided?

Thank you for your time and assistance in this project.

-Chao

helpdesk-ticket.description:
I am trying to work on a procedure for our office with regard to email addresses for students who are no longer attending.
I grabbed a random student who provided an email address on a transcript request form. I was going to see if that email address is in Jenzabar. And now I have a question.
The students is an alum from May 2015 and has not registered since.
His *EML email address is his student msoe.edu email address….which I assume is no longer active. His EML2 email address is his alumni.msoe.edu email address.
At some point, is the alumni address supposed to magically replace the student email address in *EML? Or is that a manual process that someone is supposed to be doing?
For reference, student ID# 501127.
Thanks.
Mary
Mary Nielsen Registrar Milwaukee School of Engineering Phone: 414-277-7216 Fax: 414-277-6914 www.msoe.edu

I am going to close this ticket and combine with the other one that you created regarding email process question. I believe there are jobs in Jenzabar that run that populate these email fields. But since we moved to the cloud I am not sure if they have been setup again. Getting an @alumni.msoe.edu email address into Jenzabar might be a little tricky because its currently optional for them to create an alumni account (we are considering automating alumni account creations for all graduates). Anyways I am going to forward the combined ticket to Beth and Jen since we would be the ones modifying the jobs in Jenzabar.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: MOndo Pad operation system for WebEx
helpdesk-ticket.description: We have four mondo pads in our debriefing rooms. I want to run WebEx directly from the mondo pad. However, when I open up a meeting scheduled WebEx, I get a message that the browswer, operating system does not support webEX. Can you update all four mondo pads so we can run meetings from our debriefing rooms. thanks
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
We have four mondo pads in our debriefing rooms. I want to run WebEx directly from the mondo pad. However, when I open up a meeting scheduled WebEx, I get a message that the browswer, operating system does not support webEX.

Can you update all four mondo pads so we can run meetings from our debriefing rooms.
thanks

helpdesk-note.body: sending to a/v per request.
helpdesk-note.body-html: sending to a/v per request.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jane, The Mondopad tools have their own video conference tool that competes with WebEx. The best way to run WebEx is to close the Mondopad tool itself. Use Control/Alt/Delete, and select Task Manager. End the Mondopad task. This will then make the screen appear as another monitor (without the tools). You will be able to open a browser and start your WebEx from there. If you want to go back to the Mondopad tools, click the Windows start button (lower left), and you will see Mondopad as one of the programs. Click on it and it will return to the "normal" view.
Pat Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5263 We have four mondo pads in our debriefing rooms. I want to run WebEx directly from the mondo pad. However, when I open up a meeting scheduled WebEx, I get a message that the browswer, operating system does not support webEX.
Can you update all four mondo pads so we can run meetings from our debriefing rooms.
thanks
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Jane,
The Mondopad tools have their own video conference tool that competes with WebEx. The best way to run WebEx is to close the Mondopad tool itself.
Use Control/Alt/Delete, and select Task Manager.
End the Mondopad task.
This will then make the screen appear as another monitor (without the tools). You will be able to open a browser and start your WebEx from there.
If you want to go back to the Mondopad tools, click the Windows start button (lower left), and you will see Mondopad as one of the programs. Click on it and it will return to the "normal" view.

Pat

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Jeremy.
We have tested Google drive on several other machines, both wired and wireless, with no issues. Google Drive is not blocked by MSOE. The issue is local to your laptop and we can try the following to restore service:
Uninstall/reinstall Google Drive CCleaner for registry entries that may be stopping the process reimage the C: drive when the above fail to restore service
Please visit the Help Desk so we may assist in restoring this service for you.
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Website Update
helpdesk-ticket.description:
From: Nielsen, Mary Sent: Thursday, January 28, 2016 10:33 AM To: Grennier, Dana-Marie Subject: Table required by ABET
Hi Dana—
Apparently we are required by ABET to have information about our enrollment and graduation in ABET accredited programs out on our website. I have been working with Kathy Faggiani to put together such a table. Steve Bialek told me there used to be a table that a tab for each of the programs (or at least each of the ABET programs) linked to, but I don’t know what that table looked like.
So, can we get the information in the attached spreadsheet out onto the website somehow so that we are in compliance with the ABET requirement? Kathy suggested that we put all of the programs on there not just the ABET programs, so I did that. We sort of copied Clemson’s format. http://www.clemson.edu/ces/current-students/accreditation.html
I am not sure what to do with the blank spaces for graduation numbers when we don’t have graduates yet (like for Civil and Actuarial Science)…I didn’t feel like they should be zeros. Any ideas?
Once we have the table up there, we should link it on the Right to Know Page. My understanding is that we used to have a tab for each program that linked to the table? …like a third top tab maybe? Does that ring any bells?
[cid:image001.jpg@01D159B7.43EEDD70]
I will add this to my procedures to send annual updates for the table. It will be around mid-fall quarter when the official enrollment numbers are finalized.
Mary
Mary Nielsen Registrar Milwaukee School of Engineering Phone: 414-277-7216 Fax: 414-277-6914 www.msoe.edu<http://www.msoe.edu>

So, can we get the information in the attached spreadsheet out onto the website somehow so that we are in compliance with the ABET requirement?  Kathy suggested that we put all of the programs on there not just the ABET programs, so I did that.  We sort of copied Clemson’s format. http://www.clemson.edu/ces/current-students/accreditation.html
 
I am not sure what to do with the blank spaces for graduation numbers when we don’t have graduates yet (like for Civil and Actuarial Science)…I didn’t feel like they should be zeros.  Any ideas?
 
Once we have the table up there, we should link it on the Right to Know Page.  My understanding is that we used to have a tab for each program that linked to the table? …like a third top tab maybe?  Does that ring any bells?
 
 
 
I will add this to my procedures to send annual updates for the table.  It will be around mid-fall quarter when the official enrollment numbers are finalized.
 
Mary

My first thought would be to perform a repair on Microsoft Office:
Open Control Panel and select Uninstall a Program. Select Microsoft Office Professional Plus 2013 and select the Change button at the top of the screen. Select the Repair option, and allow the wizard to run.

It is my understanding that all staff and faculty should have access to the program. I have included the necessary steps to install the Visio below. Please let us know if this solves your issue. Please note that if you are not on campus during this installation you will need to connect to globalprotect to get access to this list,.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Dr. Schilling,
Unfortunately the video you posted was too large to be uploaded, but i believe I was able to replicate the issue you were having with the south projector in L-309. The south projector was blinking on and off every 1-2 seconds. After a system reset, the projector is now only blinking every 20-30 seconds. This issue is only happening with the document camera input, all other inputs are functioning properly on both projectors. We will be working with AVI to get this issue resolved.
As a workaround until the issue is fixed, please only use the the document camera on the northern projector as this projector is not experiencing any issues. All of the other inputs to the system are functioning properly, so you can continue to use those as you normally would.
We will keep you posted with updates on this issue.
Thanks, Tim Koruna AV Student Tech

helpdesk-note.body:
The document camera was still loosing connection and blinking on and off on the south projector when I went to check on it, even after a system reset. It seems the data transfer light(orange light on the projector DM connection on DMPS unit) for the south projector was blinking, which means that the system is trying to send data but cannot establish a connection to the projector.
This behavior is only happening for the document camera input. All of the other inputs functioned normally. I'm going to assume this is something with the programming because the rest of system functions normally in every case but this. I am stumped on this so I'm guessing this is something AVI will have to take a look at.

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
For the second or third time this year, my desktop version of Outlook has stopped being able to connect after I've changed my MSOE password.

I recall having to delete some credentials in my password "vault" but don't remember the procedures. I searched the community and don't find instructions. Please provide them.

helpdesk-note.body: I went by memory and solved my own problem. Here is my documentation of the process: Problem: After doing an MSOE password change, desktop Outlook no longer connects to the server. Solution: Exit Outlook. Start Control Panel and open Credential Manager. Remove the MicrosoftOffice15_Data:SSPI:… Generic Credentials. Restart Outlook and enter your new password when prompted to do so. I urge you to post some version of these instructions on the MSOE Community page (or stop forcing PW changes until you fix this problem with Outlook and the MSOE password change process.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
I went by memory and solved my own problem. Here is my documentation of the process: 

Problem: After doing an MSOE password change, desktop Outlook no longer connects to the server.
Solution: Exit Outlook. Start Control Panel and open Credential Manager. Remove the MicrosoftOffice15_Data:SSPI:… Generic Credentials. Restart Outlook and enter your new password when prompted to do so.
I urge you to post some version of these instructions on the MSOE Community page (or stop forcing PW changes until you fix this problem with Outlook and the MSOE password change process.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Mike,
I found these instructions from Google on how to set up gmail within outlook. Alumni email accounts are hosted by Google, so this should work. I found these instructions here.
Set up Gmail with Outlook, Apple Mail, or other mail clients
You can download messages from Gmail and see them using a program like Microsoft Outlook, Apple Mail, or Thunderbird, even when you aren't online. This process is called POP or IMAP, and is free for all Gmail users.
Enable IMAP in your Gmail settings
Sign in to Gmail. Click the gear in the top right . Select Settings. Click Forwarding and POP/IMAP. Select Enable IMAP. Click Save Changes.
Note: This setting is not available while using the basic HTML view of Gmail. To enable IMAP, use the standard view instead. Find out more about standard view and basic HTML view. Once you've enabled IMAP in your Gmail settings, you need to configure your client. Select a client below to see specific configuration instructions.Outlook / Windows Mail
Open Outlook or Windows Mail. Click the Tools menu, and select Accounts or Email Accounts
Click Add. If you're setting up IMAP for the first time, confirm your settings to make sure they're correctOk, confirm my settings
Google Apps users, please follow the default instructions unless otherwise noted, replacing 'your_domain.com' with your actual domain name. Many clients will automatically configure the appropriate IMAP connection settings for your account, but confirm that the connection settings your client configures are the same as what's listed below. If you're using a client that's not listed above, you can also use the following information to configure your IMAP. If you have problems, contact your mail client's customer support department for further instructions.
Incoming Mail (IMAP) Server - Requires SSL imap.gmail.com Port: 993 Requires SSL:Yes
Outgoing Mail (SMTP) Server - Requires TLS smtp.gmail.com Port: 465 or 587 Requires SSL: Yes Requires authentication: Yes Use same settings as incoming mail server
Full Name or Display Name: [your name]
Account Name or User Name: your full Gmail address (username@gmail.com). Google Apps users, please enter username@your_domain.com
Email address: your full Gmail address (username@gmail.com) Google Apps users, please enter username@your_domain.com
Password: your Gmail password
If your client does not support SMTP authentication, you won't be able to send mail through your client using your Gmail address. Also, if you're having trouble sending mail but you've confirmed that encryption is active for SMTP in your mail client, try to configure your SMTP server on a different port: 465 or 587. Username and password not working? Some apps require you to also turn on access for less secure apps before setting up POP/IMAP connections.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Mike,

I found these instructions from Google on how to set up gmail within outlook. Alumni email accounts are hosted by Google, so this should work. I found these instructions here.

Set up Gmail with Outlook, Apple Mail, or other mail clients

You can download messages from Gmail and see them using a program like Microsoft Outlook, Apple Mail, or Thunderbird, even when you aren't online. This process is called POP or IMAP, and is free for all Gmail users.



Enable IMAP in your Gmail settings
  1. Sign in to Gmail.
  2. Click the gear in the top right .
  3. Select Settings.
  4. Click Forwarding and POP/IMAP.
  5. Select Enable IMAP.
  6. Click Save Changes.
Note: This setting is not available while using the basic HTML view of Gmail. To enable IMAP, use the standard view instead. Find out more about standard view and basic HTML view.
Once you've enabled IMAP in your Gmail settings, you need to configure your client. Select a client below to see specific configuration instructions.Outlook / Windows Mail
  1. Open Outlook or Windows Mail.
  2. Click the Tools menu, and select Accounts or Email Accounts
  3. Click Add.
If you're setting up IMAP for the first time, confirm your settings to make sure they're correctOk, confirm my settings
Google Apps users, please follow the default instructions unless otherwise noted, replacing 'your_domain.com' with your actual domain name.
Many clients will automatically configure the appropriate IMAP connection settings for your account, but confirm that the connection settings your client configures are the same as what's listed below.
If you're using a client that's not listed above, you can also use the following information to configure your IMAP. If you have problems, contact your mail client's customer support department for further instructions.
  • Incoming Mail (IMAP) Server - Requires SSL
    • imap.gmail.com
    • Port: 993
    • Requires SSL:Yes
  • Outgoing Mail (SMTP) Server - Requires TLS
    • smtp.gmail.com
    • Port: 465 or 587
    • Requires SSL: Yes
    • Requires authentication: Yes
    • Use same settings as incoming mail server
  • Full Name or Display Name: [your name]
  • Account Name or User Name: your full Gmail address (username@gmail.com). Google Apps users, please enter username@your_domain.com
  • Email address: your full Gmail address (username@gmail.com) Google Apps users, please enter username@your_domain.com
  • Password: your Gmail password
If your client does not support SMTP authentication, you won't be able to send mail through your client using your Gmail address.
Also, if you're having trouble sending mail but you've confirmed that encryption is active for SMTP in your mail client, try to configure your SMTP server on a different port: 465 or 587.
Username and password not working? Some apps require you to also turn on access for less secure apps before setting up POP/IMAP connections.

4.     Click Forwarding and POP/IMAP.
5.     Select Enable IMAP.
6.     Click Save Changes.
Note: This setting is not available while using the basic HTML view of Gmail. To enable IMAP, use the standard view instead. Find out more about standard view and basic HTML view.
Once you've enabled IMAP in your Gmail settings, you need to configure your client. Select a client below to see specific configuration instructions.Outlook / Windows Mail
1.     Open Outlook or Windows Mail.
2.     Click the Tools menu, and select Accounts or Email Accounts
3.     Click Add.
If you're setting up IMAP for the first time, confirm your settings to make sure they're correctOk, confirm my settings
Google Apps users, please follow the default instructions unless otherwise noted, replacing 'your_domain.com' with your actual domain name.
Many clients will automatically configure the appropriate IMAP connection settings for your account, but confirm that the connection settings your client configures are the same as what's listed below.
If you're using a client that's not listed above, you can also use the following information to configure your IMAP. If you have problems, contact your mail client's customer support department for further instructions.
  • Incoming Mail (IMAP) Server - Requires SSL
    • imap.gmail.com
    • Port: 993
    • Requires SSL:Yes
  • Outgoing Mail (SMTP) Server - Requires TLS
    • smtp.gmail.com
    • Port: 465 or 587
    • Requires SSL: Yes
    • Requires authentication: Yes
    • Use same settings as incoming mail server
  • Full Name or Display Name: [your name]
  • Account Name or User Name: your full Gmail address (username@gmail.com). Google Apps users, please enter username@your_domain.com
  • Email address: your full Gmail address (username@gmail.com) Google Apps users, please enter username@your_domain.com
  • Password: your Gmail password
If your client does not support SMTP authentication, you won't be able to send mail through your client using your Gmail address.
Also, if you're having trouble sending mail but you've confirmed that encryption is active for SMTP in your mail client, try to configure your SMTP server on a different port: 465 or 587.
Username and password not working? Some apps require you to also turn on access for less secure apps before setting up POP/IMAP connections.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi koleas, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5321
I have included instructions on how to set up a forwarding rule for the account. If there is no error message present when you click the "fix me" button, I will have to do some research, but I would guess it is a connection setting that needs to be changed. Are you able to send mail from the account using outlook?
Steps to Setup A Forwarding Rule 1) Open Outlook 2) On the top tab section, make sure the "Home" Tab is selected 3) In center on the tob there should be a "Rules" button with a drop down. Click it and select "Manage Rules" 4) Select "New Rule" 5) Select "Apply Rule on Messages I Receive" 6) You will want to check "Where my name is in the To or Cc Box" and click next 7) Check "Forward it to people or public group" you will notice that people or public group is in blue. 8) Once you have checked the box you will want to click on the blue text that shows up in the text box at the bottom 9) A window should pop up. In the bottom of the window, there is a box labeled, "To:" . This is where you will type your alumni email address. 10) Select Ok and the window will close. Select next, and then next again. 11) Name the rule whatever you think fits, and make sure that the checkbox for "Turn on this rule" is selected.
Please note that while setting up this walkthrough I noticed that there is a checkbox for "Run this rule for messages already in the inbox". I have not used this before, and therefore cannot guarantee it will work, however, if you check this it may your all previous emails in the inbox to your alumni email address.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

Steps to Setup A Forwarding Rule

10) Select Ok and the window will close. Select next, and then next again.
11) Name the rule whatever you think fits, and make sure that the checkbox for "Turn on this rule" is selected.

Please note that while setting up this walkthrough I noticed that there is a checkbox for "Run this rule for messages already in the inbox". I have not used this before, and therefore cannot guarantee it will work, however, if you check this it may your all previous emails in the inbox to your alumni email address.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Judah Balli, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5351
Thank you for letting us know about this issue. If we could get more information that would be great. 1. Did you open the printer on your computer and see if the documents were there in the queue? To do so: go to start, devices and printers, right click on Follow You Printing, and click on See Whats Printing. Is there an error in this page? 2. Have you waited some time before checking at the printer in case of a slow network connection? 3. How do you get your computer to print again after it fails in a given day?
James Windorff Helpdesk Technician helpdesk@msoe.edu 414 277 7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Gary, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5394
Sarah Rowell was working with Thomas on this problem. I believe we have a solution to the color printing issue that is known to work correctly.
Here is the instructions per Thomas "I was able to print in color. There is one small detail that I believe may be the cause of your issues. Follow you printing defaults to grayscale. Below I have included the steps to set the setting to color or return it to grayscale. These are done in microsoft word, and may vary slightly if using another program to print.
1) Open the document you want to print 2) Select Print 3) Select Follow You Printing 4) Under the printer there should be blue text that says "Printer Properties" 5) A new window will pop up with a variety of tabs. You will want to select the "Quality" Tab 6) Under Select Color, you will want to change it to "Auto Color" 7) Select OK and Print your document 8) Repeat steps 4-6 however, instead of selecting "Auto Color" you will want to select "Grayscale" 9) Select OK" Please let us know if you have any problems with that machine again.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Tier 2 Staff Support Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Gary,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5394

Sarah Rowell was working with Thomas on this problem. I believe we have a solution to the color printing issue that is known to work correctly.

Here is the instructions per Thomas
"I was able to print in color. There is one small detail that I believe may be the cause of your issues. Follow you printing defaults to grayscale. Below I have included the steps to set the setting to color or return it to grayscale. These are done in microsoft word, and may vary slightly if using another program to print.
 
1) Open the document you want to print
2) Select Print
3) Select Follow You Printing
4) Under the printer there should be blue text that says "Printer Properties"
5) A new window will pop up with a variety of tabs. You will want to select the "Quality" Tab
6) Under Select Color, you will want to change it to "Auto Color"
7) Select OK and Print your document
8) Repeat steps 4-6 however, instead of selecting "Auto Color" you will want to select "Grayscale"
9) Select OK"
Please let us know if you have any problems with that machine again.


Thanks,
MSOE Information Technology
Tier 2 Staff Support
Cameron Wilson
414-277-7288
helpdesk@msoe.edu
